.SH "Constructor & Destructor Documentation"
.PP 
.SS "panel::backend::BluetoothInfo::BluetoothInfo (QObject * parent = \fRnullptr\fP)\fR [explicit]\fP"

.PP
The constructor for \fR\fBBluetoothInfo\fP\fP\&. Connects to the BlueZ D-Bus service on the system bus, subscribes to \fRInterfacesAdded\fP, \fRInterfacesRemoved\fP, and \fRPropertiesChanged\fP signals, and performs an initial refresh of all managed objects\&. 
.PP
\fBParameters\fP
.RS 4
\fIparent\fP (QObject*) The parent QObject\&. 
.RE
.PP
\fBReturns\fP
.RS 4
void\&. 
.RE
.PP

.SH "Member Function Documentation"
.PP 
.SS "void panel::backend::BluetoothInfo::ConnectDevice (const QString & address)"

.PP
Initiates an asynchronous Bluetooth connection to a device\&. Sets the device's state to \fRconnecting\fP immediately, emits \fRDevicesChanged\fP, then calls \fRorg\&.bluez\&.Device1\&.Connect\fP\&. On completion, state transitions to \fRconnected\fP or \fRfailed\fP\&. 
.PP
\fBParameters\fP
.RS 4
\fIaddress\fP (const QString&) The Bluetooth address of the device to connect\&. 
.RE
.PP
\fBReturns\fP
.RS 4
void\&. 
.RE
.PP

.SS "void panel::backend::BluetoothInfo::DisconnectDevice (const QString & address)"

.PP
Initiates an asynchronous Bluetooth disconnection from a device\&. Calls \fRorg\&.bluez\&.Device1\&.Disconnect\fP asynchronously\&. 
.PP
\fBParameters\fP
.RS 4
\fIaddress\fP (const QString&) The Bluetooth address of the device to disconnect\&. 
.RE
.PP
\fBReturns\fP
.RS 4
void\&. 
.RE
.PP

